## 6. Golden Rules

1. **Backend services are REAL** -- wire up to existing endpoints, do NOT rebuild them.
2. **Max 6 files before coding** -- read only what you need (anti-context-rot).
3. **Always unwrap API envelopes** -- backend returns `{ data, meta, message }`; extract `.data`.
4. **Test before marking done** -- run `{{PKG_MANAGER}} test` and `{{PKG_MANAGER}} build`.
5. **Never touch the PROTECT LIST** -- some files are locked; check `CLAUDE.md` or ask.
6. **Multi-tenant isolation** -- EVERY database query must filter by `{{TENANT_ID_FIELD}}`.
7. **Soft delete** -- add `deletedAt: null` to every query. Never hard-delete records.
8. **One task at a time** -- finish and verify before moving to the next task.
9. **Update STATUS.md** -- mark tasks in-progress when you start, complete when you finish.
10. **Log your work** -- add entries to the work log at the end of every session.

