## 9. Code Conventions

### API Response Format
```typescript
// Backend returns this envelope -- ALWAYS unwrap in frontend
interface ApiResponse<T> {
  data: T;
  meta?: { total: number; page: number; limit: number };
  message?: string;
}

// CORRECT usage in frontend:
const response = await apiClient.get('/endpoint');
const items = response.data.data;  // Unwrap the envelope

// WRONG -- do NOT use response.data directly as your data
```

### Auth Pattern
```typescript
// Protected API calls must include auth headers
// The API client at {{FRONTEND_APP_PATH}}/lib/api.ts handles this automatically
```

### Multi-Tenant Queries
```typescript
// EVERY query must include tenant isolation
where: {
  {{TENANT_ID_FIELD}}: currentTenantId,
  deletedAt: null,
  ...filters,
}
```

### Design System
- Use `{{DESIGN_SYSTEM_LIBRARY}}` components as primitives
- Domain-specific components go in `{{COMPONENT_LIBRARY_PATH}}`
- Follow the existing naming pattern: `{Domain}{Component}.tsx`
- Always use design tokens from `{{GLOBALS_CSS_PATH}}`, not hardcoded colors

